	<annotations>
		<text id="0" type="text/plain" rect="(104.0, 358.0, 150.0, 166.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">in the distribution widget, choose the top 3 party 

conservative, labour, and liberal democrat</text>
		<text id="1" type="text/plain" rect="(263.0, 364.0, 150.0, 78.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">in the corpus, put content in text feautures</text>
		<text id="2" type="text/plain" rect="(405.0, 372.0, 150.0, 122.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">preprocess the text with transformation, tokenzation, filtering, and normalization</text>
		<text id="3" type="text/plain" rect="(508.0, 171.0, 150.0, 100.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">use bag of words to seperate the words</text>
		<text id="4" type="text/plain" rect="(453.0, -29.0, 150.0, 100.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">word cloud can be used to visualize which words are the most common </text>
		<text id="5" type="text/plain" rect="(584.0, 372.0, 150.0, 56.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">put speaker_party as the target, and selected as features</text>
		<text id="6" type="text/plain" rect="(732.0, 391.0, 150.0, 78.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">sample the data to 70-30 test and sample data</text>
		<text id="7" type="text/plain" rect="(892.0, -29.0, 150.0, 100.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">use SVM, Random forest, and logistic regression as the 3 ML models</text>
		<text id="8" type="text/plain" rect="(1173.0, 200.0, 150.0, 320.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">In the prediction results,

Logistic regression
F1 = 1.00
Prec = 1.00

Random forest
F1 = 0.834
Prec = 0.866

SVM 
F1 = 0.888
Prec = 0.857</text>
		<text id="9" type="text/plain" rect="(1318.0, 199.0, 150.0, 342.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">Judging by the performance of each ML models, we can see the logistic regression is not the best ML because it has an over-fitting problem

However, SVM has the best results with the high F1 and Prec performance</text>
		<text id="10" type="text/plain" rect="(285.0, 510.0, 150.0, 122.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">use preprocess text (Regexp and stopwords to remove the common words</text>
		<text id="11" type="text/plain" rect="(535.0, 610.0, 150.0, 100.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">conservative:
government, people, right, noble, support</text>
		<text id="12" type="text/plain" rect="(557.0, 768.0, 150.0, 29.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">labour:
govenrment, minister, people, bill</text>
		<text id="13" type="text/plain" rect="(541.0, 889.0, 150.0, 56.0)" font-family="Segoe UI" font-size="16">government, noble, lord</text>
	</annotations>
